<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">BACON-STUFFED MUSHROOMS</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page037.article003.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>


<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes about 3 dozen </p><br/><p class="no-indent">10 slices bacon </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons butter </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup finely chopped onion </p><p class="no-indent">1 teaspoon minced garlic </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons bourbon </p><p class="no-indent">1 (8-ounce) package cream cheese, softened </p><p class="no-indent">2½ pounds fresh button mushrooms, stems removed </p><p class="no-indent">Garnish: chopped fresh thyme </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350˚. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon to drain on paper towels, discarding drippings. Wipe skillet clean. Crumble bacon.</p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. In skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Remove from heat, and add bacon and bourbon. Return to heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until bourbon is evaporated. Reduce heat to low. Add cream cheese, stirring until mixture is combined. Spoon mixture into mushroom caps, and place on prepared baking sheet. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Garnish with chopped fresh thyme, if desired. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">Tip: Buy mushrooms that are all about the same size for even baking and a prettier presentation.</p></div>
